-- Brazil's Oi signs agreement with Portugal Telecom to save merger
-- By Reese Ewing
-- Wed Jul 16, 2014 06:33AM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, July 16 (Reuters) - Brazil's Grupo Oi SA <OIBR3.SA> said in a market filing early on Wednesday that it had signed a memorandum of understanding with Portugal Telecom <PTC.LS> to protect their merger and give Oi guarantees against potential losses from an investment in Rioforte.   (Reporting by Reese Ewing; Editing by Lisa Von Ahn)  ((reese.ewing@thomsonreuters.com)(+5511 5644 7721)(Reuters Messaging: reese.ewing.thomsonreuters@thomsonreuters.net))  Keywords: BES EXPOSUREOI SA

